function search_sync(schema: <link xref="Secret.Schema">Secret.Schema</link>, attributes: {String: String}, flags: <link xref="Secret.SearchFlags">Secret.SearchFlags</link>, cancellable: <link href="../Gio-2.0/Gio.Cancellable.html">Gio.Cancellable</link>): Array(<link xref="Secret.Item">Secret.Item</link>) {
    // Gjs wrapper for secret_collection_search_sync()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Search for items matching the <code>attributes</code> in the @collection.
The <code>attributes</code> should be a table of string keys and string values.</p>  <p>If <link xref="Secret.SearchFlags"/>.all is set in <code>flags</code>, then all the items matching the
search will be returned. Otherwise only the first item will be returned.
This is almost always the unlocked item that was most recently stored.</p>  <p>If <link xref="Secret.SearchFlags"/>.unlock is set in <code>flags</code>, then items will be unlocked
if necessary. In either case, locked and unlocked items will match the
search and be returned. If the unlock fails, the search does not fail.</p>  <p>If <link xref="Secret.SearchFlags"/>.load_secrets is set in <code>flags</code>, then the items will have
their secret values loaded and available via <link xref="Secret.Item.get_secret"/>.</p>  <p>This function may block indefinetely. Use the asynchronous version
in user interface threads.</p>

